<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Pokémon API Home</title>
    <link href="/css/index.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body>

    <header class="index-header">
        <h1>Pokémon API</h1>
        <p>Explore the world of Pokémon through our API</p>
    </header>

    <section class="index-section">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Retrieve detailed information about specific Pokémon</li>
            <li>Search for Pokémon based on various criteria</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="index-section">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>

        <div class="endpoint">
            <code class="index-code">GET /api/0.0.1/pokemon</code>
            <p>Retrieve a list of all available Pokémon.</p>
            <div class="example">
                <span>Example:</span>
                <pre>curl -X GET https://app-domain.com/api/0.0.1/pokemon</pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="endpoint">
            <code class="index-code">GET /api/0.0.1/pokemon/{id or name}</code>
            <p>Retrieve detailed information about a specific Pokémon based on its ID or name.</p>
            <div class="example">
                <span>Example:</span>
                <pre>curl -X GET https://app-domain.com/api/0.0.1/pokemon/25</pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="endpoint">
            <code class="index-code">POST /api/0.0.1/pokemon/search</code>
            <p>Retrieve Pokémon based on certain criteria. Provide the criteria in the request body.</p>
            <div class="example">
                <span>Example:</span>
                <pre>curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"type": "electric"}' https://app-domain.com/api/0.0.1/pokemon/search</pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="index-footer">
        <p>&copy; 2023 Pokémon API. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

</body>

</html>
